Hello Frank,
 
On the Domain Controller and workstations of the CT Scanner network the Cumulative Update of October was still running (2022-10 Cumulative Update for Windows Server 2016 for x64-based Systems (KB5018411).
The update of November (2022-11 Cumulative Update for Windows Server 2016 for x64-based Systems KB5019964) has not been installed on purpose because of problems with Kerberos.
 
In the meantime we skipped CU 2022-11 and last Monday 2022-12 Cumulative Update for Windows Server 2016 for x64-based Systems (KB5021235) was installed.
Last Monday the workstation in the CMH was also replaced. Both actions did not solve the problem on the workstation in the CMH (see attached: Fout_IntelliSpacePortal.JPG).
 
During startup of the IntelliSpacePortal (on the workstation) we made a number of network captures and see in it that the communication between the workstations and the ISP11MASTER (10.14.80.3) is not working entirely well (see attached: Capture_ISP_CMH.JPG). The other network traffic between the workstations and for example the Domain Controller on Schiphol went without any problems. We also see similar messages in the communication between the workstation in Maasland and the ISP11Master.
 
The Domain Controller and the ISP11MASTER are at Schiphol in the same switch.
 
Also added the capture file that can be opened with Wireshark (attached: Capture_ISP_CMH.pcapng).
On this there is a filter for the overview in Wireshark so only traffic from and to the 10.14.80.3 can be seen.
 
What we already noticed since the installation of the ISP11MASTER is that on the workstations (when starting the IntelliSpacePortal) it takes at least 8 to 10 seconds before the Authentication Source (CTD) appears.
And since recently the Authentication Source no longer appears in the CMH.
 
Could you check on the ISP11MASTER what could be the reason for the Reset (RST) and Retransmissions in the communication between workstation and ISP server?
 
Thanks in advance.
Sincerely

Subject: RE: Eventlogs Windows workstation CMH Utrecht
 
Dear Guido,
 
We have checked the event logs of the client and do see a number of errors that are related to the connection with domain controller. Among other:

The processing of Group Policy failed because of lack of network connectivity to a domain controller. This may be a transient condition. A success message would be generated once the machine gets connected to the domain controller and Group Policy has successfully processed. If you do not see a success message for several hours, then contact your administrator.

This computer was not able to set up a secure session with a domain controller in domain CTD due to the following: 
We cannot sign you in with this credential because your domain isn't available. Make sure your device is connected to your organization's network and try again. If you previously signed in on this device with another credential, you can sign in with that credential. 
This may lead to authentication problems. Make sure that this computer is connected to the network. If the problem persists, please contact your domain administrator.  
 
ADDITIONAL INFO: 
If this computer is a domain controller for the specified domain, it sets up the secure session to the primary domain controller emulator in the specified domain. Otherwise, this computer sets up the secure session to any domain controller in the specified domain.

We also see DCOM warnings:

The application-specific permission settings do not grant Local Launch permission for the COM Server application with CLSID 
Windows.SecurityCenter.SecurityAppBroker
And APPID 
Unavailable
To the user NT AUTHORITY\SYSTEM SID (S-1-5-18) from address LocalHost (Using LRPC) running in the application container Unavailable SID (Unavailable). This security permission can be modified using the Component Services administrative tool.


In the meantime we also received similar messages from another customer which makes us suspect that it could be a Windows patch on the domain server. Can you check if you accidentally patched the domain server with KB5019964?
This can namely explain the problems you are experiencing.
The solution for this is patch: KB5021235
 
Please let me know.
 
 
Kind regards,

Translated Description:
Caution: This e-mail originated from outside of Philips, be careful for phishing. 

Best

Several users no longer get to see ROI values and 3D measurement values in IntelliSpace Portal when they go to Step 2 on a CTA STROKE examination in Brain Perfusion.
Under Brain Perfusion they select an Artery and Vein via 'use for calculation', after which they click on the arrow to go to Perfusion Maps:
 

In Perfusion Maps all images are then well visible, but there are no values with ROI measurements or 3D measurements:
 

The error message they see is: "Scan duration is shorter than the "Permeability scan duration" value in the Perfusion Maps Parameters tab, therefore, permeability measurements are not available.":
 

Is this a known problem?
How can we get the values visible again?

Sincerely

Tim Polman

Translated Short Description: PACS Integration IntellisPace Portal does not function optimally
Translated Description:
Gentlemen of the service desk,

Can one of you create a case for the master server of ISP in MST Enschede (NZW514). This can be booked in the name of Richard van der Plas.
Concerns the URL integration from Synapse PACS to IntelliSpace Portal. This integration does not seem to be working correctly. At first use the integration starts normally. When changing to another patient the Portal/plugin should close. This does not happen. When selecting a new case the Portal does not want to start because it is still open or seems to be open. Hard closing is a workaround, but not desired. 
The procedure should be that the application/opened application closes if a user in PACS goes to another patient, but Portal as program must remain available in the background. For the next case it can then be opened quickly. 

Can you check in consultation with MST if the contents of the URL are correct?
Thanks in advance for processing.

Sincerely

Arno Antuma
Application Consultant IntelliSpace Portal
Philips Health Systems Benelux

High Tech Campus 52, 5656 AG Eindhoven
Tel: +31 (0) 6 3926 5982, E-mail: arno.antuma@philips.com

Helpdesk: +31 (0) 40 700 12 10 option 2 - 4 - 5, servicedesk.isp@philips.com 

Absent on Fridays
More information about IntelliSpace Portal
 
Connect with Philips

Translated Description:
Dear PMS Response Team,
 
Hereby we would like to have Your support with respect to the following:

1. Equipment details
Equipment model                    IntelliSpace Portal                                 
SW. Rel:                                  10.1.3.32808
SN                                           702785
Installed Product ID                 83075574

2. Problem description

The customer complained that the patients have disappeared from one of the configured folders. When we check, the patients are on the folder in Windows, but do not appear on the SW.
We tried to do an Upgrade All from the Portal Management Tool, but it gives directly the message ?Upgrade completed?. When we try ?Rebuild All?, on the Local folder appear only 300-400 patients, and on the ?Backup? folder that had previously disappeared shows only a few patients. 

We were wondering if it is possible to reinstall the SW from scratch, but we only can find FCO88100078, and as far as we can see it is not an installation from scratch.

Could you please send us the link to download the complete installation files in order to perform a clean install?


Best regards
Unicare Service Team

Translated Short Description: Potential incorrect measurement result from ISP TAVI planning
Translated Description: Potential incorrect measurement result from ISP TAVI planning. We have noticed a potentially significant difference concerning patient care and the measurement results which are provided in the TAVI PLANNING-tool, depending on which version that was actual during the time of measurement. The final TAVI-unit dimension is normally 2mm bigger than the results which are provided from splice-contour measurement in the first phase of TAVI-planning. It should be noted that in these two measurements, the measurement object is exactly the same and measurement points are set on the same. Attached two patient examples. They were never sent, they are anonymizing and sending the examples to me as-of-writing. We have used the results of unit size to make the decision on choice of valve. If this measurement is too big, this could potentially lead to a choice of wrong valve design and size which in turn can lead to aplication. This matter was brought to our attention recently since the analysis of a few patient with 3Mensio software, which results were regularly a couple of mm smaller than the measurements form our tool for choice of size of units. In other word, the results from Philips software and 3Mensio were not matching each other.

Translated Description:
Caution: This e-mail originated from outside of Philips, be careful for phishing. 

Best

We see in our monitoring system that IntelliSpace Portal is frequently not accessible via the network.
It mainly is bldisp (virtual server), bldispm01 (master) and bldispb01 (backup). The slave and test server do not have these problems.

We see in the event viewer on the servers no errors/warnings that explain the failures.
Nor is it a restart (the uptime on the servers is longer than the moments where the failure was).
Network management of the UMC indicates that they see no errors/failures on the network connections of the servers.

In the attachments screenshots from our monitoring program.

Does Philips have any idea what could cause this?

Sincerely

Tim Polman

Translated Description:
Dear Team,
Good afternoon.
We are facing a very strange issue on an ISP IX/LX (original 11.1.1) since more than a year now. I have contacted pms response in Dec 2022 (Case Number 0120955912) but since i was not trained, I didn?t get help but got below advise:
The reason why you are facing issues is because the system is NOT configured at all: system doesn?t have an IP address; CCT tool is not configured; ISP version not defined for licensing.
Our conclusion is that the system is not installed correctly, this must be done by a certified engineer.

Today im nearly done with my training and my trainer told me that i can contact ICAP team for help so kindly find below summary, also If it was installed incorrectly, why did it worked and tested by client for sometimes then fail?

I install the system end 2020 and it has been working fine for a year. Then we first got the issue:
-	Client can?t connect anymore to app. Error network adapter.
-	FSE_admin also cannot connect. I get error please verify your network configuration and another error verify portal installation.
-	I have tried reactivating in CCT but error license check fail.
-	Have tried activation in postinstallation tools and it was successful but still same error.
-	Have tried everything and end up reloading complete os and app.

It worked well for three months then same issue.

Have updated to 11.1.3 got the license updated and it again worked for some months then same issue again.

From there I reinstalled 5 times and last Monday issue came again, note that system is not connected to internet and no windows update applied.

Below link to log and attached some pictures for info.
https://we.tl/t-NqJtgmuUTB

The client is fuming and we really can?t continue to reload os and app every 1 or 2 months. If issue was from our side, I would have understand but system cannot work after a fresh install then fail later. Can you please help.

System ISP IX/LX
SN 704037


Best Regards,

ASHLEY MODLAMOOTOO (he,him)
TEAM LEADER MEDICAL SERVICE

Translated Description:
Rens,

Zou je een case voor mij kunnen aanmaken voor ziekenhuis IJsselland Capelle ad IJssel op naam van Robert Spoel?
Betreft onderstaande informatie met als titel ?Autoprocessing ClearRead CAD fails during processing?

ClearRead CAD and (Philips CT Incisive) data compatibility
Customer would like to use ClearRead CAD for autodetection of nodules based on Chest CTs of their Incisive CT. 
Auto processing rules are set in the preferences (based on series description) and processing is starting, however fails somewhere in the process.
Semi-automatic processing (via run processing -> LNA Algorithms) succeed and results are available. 
 
Screenshot shows a serie with 3 'images' based on autoprocessing, LNA does not show results in LNA application and a serie with 12 'images' based on semi-automatic processing which shows the CAD suggestions in the LNA app and in MMV. 
 
My question is: What can cause the fail of automatic processing which is starting. Issue is specific seen on Incisive Scandata.

Ik zal een en ander escaleren.
Dank alvast!

Met vriendelijke groet,

Arno Antuma
Application Consultant IntelliSpace Portal
